---
<BaseLayout
  title="The Foundry Edison — Vintage Décor | Archipelago Lighting Group"
  description="The Foundry Edison: squirrel-cage filament geometry, 2200K candle-hour CCT, CRI 90+, dimmable to 5%. ST19 and ST21 envelopes. The Vintage Décor Edison lamp."
  bodyClass="page-edison-family"
>
<style>
  :root {
    --ed-brick: #8B3A2A;
    --ed-cream: #EFE6D2;
    --ed-cream2: #E5D9C0;
    --ed-ink: #1A130A;
    --ed-umber: #1C0F06;
    --ed-sans: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
    --ed-serif: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif;
    --ed-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace;
  }
  .ed-cream  { background: var(--ed-cream); color: var(--ed-ink); }
  .ed-cream2 { background: var(--ed-cream2); color: var(--ed-ink); }
  .ed-umber  { background: var(--ed-umber); color: #EFE6D2; }
  .ed-eyebrow { font-family: var(--ed-mono); font-size: 0.68rem; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .ed-eyebrow-rule::before { content: ""; display: inline-block; width: 28px; height: 1px; background: var(--ed-brick); vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 12px; }
  .ed-eyebrow-rule-light::before { background: rgba(245,194,74,0.7); }
  .ed-brick-text { color: var(--ed-brick); }
  .ed-h1 { font-family: var(--ed-serif); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.05; }
  .ed-h2 { font-family: var(--ed-serif); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.1; }
  .ed-serif-text { font-family: var(--ed-serif); }
  .ed-stat-num { font-family: var(--ed-sans); font-weight: 900; font-size: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1; color: var(--ed-brick); }
  .ed-stat-label { font-family: var(--ed-mono); font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; opacity: 0.65; margin-top: 4px; }
  .ed-btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; padding: 12px 24px; font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; border: none; transition: background 0.15s; font-family: var(--ed-mono); }
  .ed-btn-primary { background: var(--ed-brick); color: white; }
  .ed-btn-primary:hover { background: #6e2d1f; }
  .ed-btn-outline { background: transparent; color: var(--ed-ink); border: 1.5px solid rgba(26,19,10,0.3); }
  .ed-btn-outline:hover { border-color: var(--ed-ink); }
  .ed-btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: var(--ed-ink); }
  .ed-btn-ghost:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .ed-trust-badge { font-family: var(--ed-mono); font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 4px 10px; border: 1px solid rgba(26,19,10,0.2); display: inline-block; }
  .ed-photo-ph { background: #1C0F06; aspect-ratio: 4/3; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; }
  .ed-photo-ph-text { font-family: var(--ed-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; padding: 2rem; border: 1px dashed rgba(239,230,210,0.15); margin: 2rem; color: rgba(239,230,210,0.4); }
  .ed-spec-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr; gap: 1rem; padding: 0.75rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26,19,10,0.08); font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .ed-spec-row dt { font-family: var(--ed-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; opacity: 0.7; }
  .ed-spec-row dd { margin: 0; font-family: var(--ed-serif); }
  .ed-spec-block-num { font-family: var(--ed-mono); font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.18em; color: var(--ed-brick); }
  .ed-sku-table { width: 100%; background: white; border: 1px solid rgba(26,19,10,0.1); font-family: var(--ed-mono); font-size: 0.68rem; }
  .ed-sku-table th { padding: 0.75rem 1rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26,19,10,0.1); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em; opacity: 0.7; }
  .ed-sku-table td { padding: 0.6rem 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26,19,10,0.06); }
  .ed-sku-table tr:hover td { background: rgba(139,58,42,0.04); }
  .ed-sister-card { display: block; padding: 1.25rem; border: 1px solid rgba(26,19,10,0.1); background: var(--ed-cream); text-decoration: none; color: inherit; transition: border-color 0.15s; }
  .ed-sister-card:hover { border-color: var(--ed-brick); }
  .ed-breadcrumb { border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26,19,10,0.1); background: white; }
  .ed-breadcrumb__inner { max-width: 1536px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 12px 24px; font-family: var(--ed-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; opacity: 0.7; }
  .ed-breadcrumb a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }
  .ed-breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--ed-brick); opacity: 1; }
  .ed-callout-ey { font-family: var(--ed-mono); font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #6e3a10; }
</style>

<div class="ed-breadcrumb">
  <div class="ed-breadcrumb__inner">
    <a href="/">HOME</a> ›
    <a href="/products/">PRODUCTS</a> ›
    <a href="/products/lamps/">LAMPS</a> ›
    <a href="/collections/vintage-decor/">VINTAGE DÉCOR</a> ›
    THE FOUNDRY EDISON
  </div>
</div>

<main id="main">

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="ed-cream" aria-labelledby="ed-hero-h1">
  <div style="max-width:1536px;margin:0 auto;padding:4rem 1.5rem;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:3rem;align-items:center;" class="ed-hero-grid">
    <div class="ed-photo-ph lifestyle-photo">
      <div class="ed-photo-ph-text lifestyle-photo">LIFESTYLE PHOTOGRAPHY<br><span style="opacity:0.6;">— ROOSTER CREATIVE DELIVERABLE —</span><br><br><span style="opacity:0.5;">FOUNDRY EDISON IN INDUSTRIAL LOFT SETTING<br>BARE-BULB PENDANT · SQUIRREL-CAGE FILAMENT VISIBLE</span></div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="ed-eyebrow ed-eyebrow-rule" style="opacity:0.6;margin-bottom:1.5rem;"><span class="ed-brick-text">SERIES ·</span> VINTAGE DÉCOR · INDUSTRIAL REVIVAL</p>
      <h1 id="ed-hero-h1" class="ed-h1" style="font-size:clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem);margin-bottom:1rem;">The Foundry Edison</h1>
      <p class="ed-serif-text" style="font-size:1.25rem;font-style:italic;margin-bottom:1.5rem;opacity:0.9;">The squirrel-cage filament drawn to look like 1908.</p>
      <p class="ed-serif-text" style="font-size:1rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:2rem;opacity:0.85;max-width:36rem;">Multiple parallel LED-on-glass strands shaped into the cylindrical squirrel-cage geometry that defined Edison's 1880s carbon-filament lamps. Clear or amber glass, 2200K candle-hour CCT, and a filament that renders the second-half-of-evening register without the soot of the original. For restaurant pendant arrays, industrial revival lofts, and heritage hotel lobbies where the lamp is the architectural statement.</p>
      <dl style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1.25rem 2rem;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <div><dd class="ed-stat-num">2.5–6.0W</dd><dt class="ed-stat-label">Input wattage range</dt></div>
        <div><dd class="ed-stat-num">280–550 lm</dd><dt class="ed-stat-label">Lumen output</dt></div>
        <div><dd class="ed-stat-num">2200K</dd><dt class="ed-stat-label">Candle hour CCT</dt></div>
        <div><dd class="ed-stat-num">CRI 90+</dd><dt class="ed-stat-label">Color fidelity</dt></div>
      </dl>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        <span class="ed-trust-badge">CRI 90+</span>
        <span class="ed-trust-badge">UL LISTED</span>
        <span class="ed-trust-badge">CEC TITLE 24 JA8</span>
        <span class="ed-trust-badge">DIMMABLE TO 5%</span>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:12px;">
        <a href="/support/sample-request?subject=Foundry+Edison+Spec" class="ed-btn ed-btn-primary">SPECIFY THIS LAMP</a>
        <a href="/support/sample-request?subject=Foundry+Edison+Sample" class="ed-btn ed-btn-outline">REQUEST SAMPLE</a>
        <a href="#resources" class="ed-btn ed-btn-ghost">DOCUMENTATION ↓</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<style>
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .ed-hero-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; } }
</style>

<!-- WHERE IT BELONGS -->
<section class="ed-cream2" aria-labelledby="ed-belongs-h2">
  <div style="max-width:1536px;margin:0 auto;padding:5rem 1.5rem;">
    <p class="ed-eyebrow ed-eyebrow-rule ed-brick-text" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">WHERE THE FOUNDRY BELONGS</p>
    <h2 id="ed-belongs-h2" class="ed-h2" style="font-size:clamp(1.75rem,3.5vw,3rem);margin-bottom:3rem;">Three install registers. One lamp.</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1.5rem;" class="ed-belongs-grid">
      <div style="background:var(--ed-cream);padding:1.5rem;border:1px solid rgba(26,19,10,0.1);">
        <p class="ed-callout-ey" style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">RESTAURANT · BARE-BULB PENDANT</p>
        <h3 class="ed-serif-text" style="font-size:1.25rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">The tubular lamp on its own cord.</h3>
        <p style="font-size:0.85rem;line-height:1.7;opacity:0.85;font-family:var(--ed-serif);">Restaurant pendant arrays. Speakeasy and craft-cocktail bars. Coffee-shop ambient overheads. Clear glass shows the filament; 2200K CCT renders skin tones in the second-half-of-evening register without the soot of the original lamp.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--ed-cream);padding:1.5rem;border:1px solid rgba(26,19,10,0.1);">
        <p class="ed-callout-ey" style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">INDUSTRIAL REVIVAL · LOFT &amp; TAPROOM</p>
        <h3 class="ed-serif-text" style="font-size:1.25rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">The lamp that earns the building.</h3>
        <p style="font-size:0.85rem;line-height:1.7;opacity:0.85;font-family:var(--ed-serif);">Converted warehouse lofts, craft taprooms, maker-space studios. The squirrel-cage filament is the architectural detail — the lamp is the reason to leave the bulb exposed. Amber glass deepens the industrial register.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--ed-cream);padding:1.5rem;border:1px solid rgba(26,19,10,0.1);">
        <p class="ed-callout-ey" style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">HOSPITALITY · HERITAGE BUILDINGS</p>
        <h3 class="ed-serif-text" style="font-size:1.25rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">200 lamps. One historical reference.</h3>
        <p style="font-size:0.85rem;line-height:1.7;opacity:0.85;font-family:var(--ed-serif);">Boutique hotels in pre-war buildings, restored grand hotels, restaurants in heritage interiors. Heritage binning kits ship 3-step MacAdam matched samples for the lobby chandelier where the period accuracy matters.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <style>
      @media (max-width: 768px) { .ed-belongs-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; } }
    </style>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FILAMENT TECHNOLOGY SPOTLIGHT -->
<section class="ed-umber" aria-labelledby="ed-filament-h2">
  <div style="max-width:1536px;margin:0 auto;padding:5rem 1.5rem;">
    <p class="ed-eyebrow ed-eyebrow-rule ed-eyebrow-rule-light" style="color:rgba(245,194,74,0.85);margin-bottom:1.5rem;">FILAMENT TECHNOLOGY · SQUIRREL-CAGE GEOMETRY</p>
    <h2 id="ed-filament-h2" class="ed-h2" style="font-size:clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.5rem);margin-bottom:1.5rem;max-width:48rem;">A filament drawn to look like 1908. Behavior tuned to 2026.</h2>
    <p class="ed-serif-text" style="font-size:1rem;opacity:0.8;max-width:48rem;margin-bottom:3rem;line-height:1.75;">Multiple parallel LED-on-glass strands shaped into the cylindrical squirrel-cage geometry that defined Edison's 1880s carbon-filament lamps. The strands sit in clear or amber glass; the cage structure is visible at every install register. Operationally: 25,000-hour life, full TRIAC and ELV dimming, 70% energy reduction over the carbon-filament originals these lamps were built to evoke.</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:3rem;" class="ed-filament-grid">
      <div>
        <p style="font-family:var(--ed-mono);font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.18em;color:rgba(245,194,74,0.85);margin-bottom:0.75rem;">— PARALLEL CAGE</p>
        <p class="ed-serif-text" style="font-size:0.9rem;opacity:0.85;line-height:1.7;">Six to eight LED strands arranged in a cylindrical pattern matching the original squirrel-cage carbon-filament dimensions. Visible at every viewing angle.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p style="font-family:var(--ed-mono);font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.18em;color:rgba(245,194,74,0.85);margin-bottom:0.75rem;">— COLOR REGISTER</p>
        <p class="ed-serif-text" style="font-size:0.9rem;opacity:0.85;line-height:1.7;">2200K candle-hour CCT renders amber-warm without the sooty cast of older "warm white" LEDs. Intentional approximation of the candle-to-Edison transition register.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p style="font-family:var(--ed-mono);font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.18em;color:rgba(245,194,74,0.85);margin-bottom:0.75rem;">— HISTORICAL REFERENCE</p>
        <p class="ed-serif-text" style="font-size:0.9rem;opacity:0.85;line-height:1.7;">Filament geometry documented against pre-1940 lamp catalogs and restoration architect references. ST19 envelope dimensions match originals to within 1mm.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <style>
      @media (max-width: 768px) { .ed-filament-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; } }
    </style>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- STRUCTURED SPECS -->
<section class="ed-cream" aria-labelledby="ed-specs-h2">
  <div style="max-width:1536px;margin:0 auto;padding:5rem 1.5rem;">
    <p class="ed-eyebrow ed-eyebrow-rule ed-brick-text" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">FULL SPECIFICATIONS</p>
    <h2 id="ed-specs-h2" class="ed-h2" style="font-size:clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.5rem);margin-bottom:3rem;">Spec sheet for the lamp · restoration-grade detail.</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:220px 1fr;gap:3rem;align-items:start;" class="ed-spec-grid">
      <aside aria-label="Spec sections" style="position:sticky;top:1.5rem;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--ed-mono);font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.18em;opacity:0.55;margin-bottom:0.75rem;padding:0 0.75rem;">SPEC SECTIONS</p>
        <nav style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.25rem;">
          <a href="#spec-color" class="toc-link active"><span style="font-family:var(--ed-mono);font-size:0.65rem;opacity:0.55;">01</span> Color &amp; Filament</a>
          <a href="#spec-electrical" class="toc-link"><span style="font-family:var(--ed-mono);font-size:0.65rem;opacity:0.55;">02</span> Electrical</a>
          <a href="#spec-dimming" class="toc-link"><span style="font-family:var(--ed-mono);font-size:0.65rem;opacity:0.55;">03</span> Dimming &amp; Controls</a>
          <a href="#spec-materials" class="toc-link"><span style="font-family:var(--ed-mono);font-size:0.65rem;opacity:0.55;">04</span> Materials &amp; Finish</a>
          <a href="#spec-compliance" class="toc-link"><span style="font-family:var(--ed-mono);font-size:0.65rem;opacity:0.55;">05</span> Compliance &amp; Warranty</a>
        </nav>
      </aside>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:3rem;">
      <article id="spec-color">
        <p class="ed-spec-block-num" style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">01</p>
        <h3 class="ed-serif-text" style="font-size:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">Color &amp; Filament</h3>
        <dl>
          <div class="ed-spec-row"><dt>CCT</dt><dd>2200K (candle-hour) · 2700K (on select JA8 variants)</dd></div>
          <div class="ed-spec-row"><dt>CRI</dt><dd>≥90</dd></div>
          <div class="ed-spec-row"><dt>Filament geometry</dt><dd>Squirrel-cage · cylindrical · 6–8 parallel strands</dd></div>
          <div class="ed-spec-row"><dt>Glass finish</dt><dd>
            <span class="swatch" style="background:rgba(239,230,210,0.5);border:1px solid rgba(26,19,10,0.3);" title="Clear"></span><span style="font-size:0.85rem;">Clear (C)</span>
            &nbsp;
            <span class="swatch" style="background:#C7822E;" title="Amber"></span><span style="font-size:0.85rem;">Amber (V · X)</span>
            &nbsp;
            <span class="swatch" style="background:#6E5236;" title="Smoked"></span><span style="font-size:0.85rem;">Smoked (M)</span>
          </dd></div>
